Being short-sighted, some may believe decline in skilled workers could benefit skilled British nations due to simple supply: demand logic. But I believe a potential bubbling benefit to a slightly more homogeneous population, due to supply: demand ratio will burst due to a gradual population skill gap impacting on the wider economy and thus jobs.
